=head1 DESCRIPTION

An object that provides the current value of a security control
parameter and identifies whether it has been customized.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 Value => L<Paws::SecurityHub::ParameterValue>

The current value of a control parameter.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> ValueType => Str

Identifies whether a control parameter uses a custom user-defined value
or subscribes to the default Security Hub behavior.

When C<ValueType> is set equal to C<DEFAULT>, the default behavior can
be a specific Security Hub default value, or the default behavior can
be to ignore a specific parameter. When C<ValueType> is set equal to
C<DEFAULT>, Security Hub ignores user-provided input for the C<Value>
field.

When C<ValueType> is set equal to C<CUSTOM>, the C<Value> field can't
be empty.



